## 1. Logging In

Navigate to the admin panel URL and sign in with your administrator credentials.

![Admin Login Screen](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/admin_login_screen_1773191011354.png)

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **Email** | Your admin email address |
| **Password** | Your admin password |

- Click **Sign In** to access the dashboard
- Click **← Back to Website** to return to the public site

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Only users with the [admin](file:///Users/yujithperera/Documents/Gracelogistics_V5/admin) role can access the admin panel. Regular customers will be denied access.

---

## 2. Dashboard Overview

The landing page after login. Shows a high-level summary of your platform data at a glance.

![Dashboard Overview](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_overview_1773191169372.png)

### Summary Cards

| Card | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **Total Rates** | Total number of freight rate entries in the system |
| **Active Rates** | Number of rates currently marked as active |
| **Customers** | Number of registered customer accounts |
| **Ports** | Total ports available in the system |

### Sidebar Navigation

The left sidebar provides quick access to all admin sections. The currently logged-in user's email and a **Log Out** button are shown at the bottom of the sidebar.

---

## 3. Rate Management

The core section for managing freight rate quotes that customers see on the public rates page.

![Rate Management](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_rates_1773191173338.png)

### Filters

Use the dropdown filters at the top to narrow down displayed rates:

| Filter | Options |
|--------|---------|
| **Origin** | Filter by port of loading |
| **Destination** | Filter by port of discharge |
| **Tier** | Filter by pricing tier (Public, Tier 1, etc.) |
| **Status** | Filter by Active or Inactive |

Click **Clear** to reset all filters.

### Rate Table Columns

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Origin** | Port of loading (city + country) |
| **Destination** | Port of discharge (city + country) |
| **Container** | Container type (e.g., 20' Dry Standard) |
| **Tier** | Pricing tier this rate belongs to (Public = visible to all) |
| **Rate (USD)** | Price per container in US Dollars |
| **Transit** | Transit time in days (optional) |
| **Valid From** | Start date of rate validity |
| **Valid To** | End date of rate validity |
| **Status** | Active (green) or Inactive |

### Actions

| Button | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **+ New Rate** | Opens a form to create a new freight rate |
| **Download CSV** | Exports all rates as a CSV file |
| **Edit** | Modify an existing rate's details |
| **Dup** | Duplicate a rate (useful for creating similar rates) |
| **Del** | Delete a rate (with confirmation) |

### Creating a New Rate

1. Click **+ New Rate** in the top-right corner
2. Fill in the required fields:
   - **Origin Port** and **Destination Port** (select from dropdowns)
   - **Container Type** (select from configured types)
   - **Rate (USD)** — the price per container
   - **Pricing Tier** — which customer tier can see this rate
   - **Valid From / Valid To** dates
   - **Transit Days** (optional)
3. Click **Save** to publish the rate

> [!TIP]
> Use the **Dup** (duplicate) button to quickly create a variant of an existing rate — for example, the same route with a different container type or tier.

---

## 4. User Management

Manage all customer accounts, including their roles, companies, pricing tiers, and approval status.

![User Management](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_users_1773191177170.png)

### User Table Columns

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Name** | Customer's full name |
| **Email** | Account email address |
| **Company** | Company/organization name |
| **Role** | `customer` or [admin](file:///Users/yujithperera/Documents/Gracelogistics_V5/admin) |
| **Pricing Tier** | Which pricing tier this user belongs to |
| **Status** | Active (green) or Inactive |
| **Created** | Account creation date |

### Actions

| Button | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **+ New User** | Create a new customer account |
| **Edit** | Modify user details, change tier, or deactivate |

### Editing a User

Click the **Edit** button next to any user to modify:
- **Name**, **Company** — update profile information
- **Pricing Tier** — switch between Public, Tier 1, etc. to control which rates they see
- **Status** — set to Active or Inactive to enable/disable account access
- **Role** — change between `customer` and [admin](file:///Users/yujithperera/Documents/Gracelogistics_V5/admin)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Changing a user's **Pricing Tier** immediately affects which rates they see on the public rates page. Customers on "Public" tier only see public rates. Customers on "Tier 1" see Tier 1 rates (typically better pricing).

---

## 5. Port Management

Manage the ports available for origin/destination selection in rate entries and the public search form.

![Port Management](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_ports_1773191180962.png)

### Port Table Columns

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Name** | Port city name (e.g., Shanghai, Colombo) |
| **Country** | Country the port belongs to |
| **Port Code** | International port code (e.g., CNSHA, LKCMB) |
| **Created** | Date the port was added |

### Actions

| Button | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **+ New Port** | Add a new port to the system |
| **Edit** | Modify port name, country, or code |
| **Del** | Remove a port (only if not used in any rates) |

### Adding a New Port

1. Click **+ New Port**
2. Enter the **Port Name**, **Country**, and **Port Code**
3. Click **Save**

> [!NOTE]
> Port codes follow the UN/LOCODE format (e.g., CNSHA for Shanghai, China). You can look up codes at [unece.org](https://unece.org/trade/cefact/UNLOCODE-Download).

---

## 6. Container Types

Configure the container types available for rate entries (e.g., 20' Dry Standard, 40' High Cube).

![Container Types](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_container_types_1773191206061.png)

### Managing Container Types

- Click **+ New Type** to add a container type
- Each type has a **Name** (displayed to customers) and a **Code** (internal identifier)
- Use **Edit** to rename or update a container type
- Use **Del** to remove (only if not referenced by existing rates)

### Common Container Types

| Container | Typical Use |
|-----------|-------------|
| 20' Dry Standard | General cargo, most common |
| 40' Dry Standard | Larger general cargo shipments |
| 40' Dry High Cube | Bulky/light cargo needing extra height |
| 20' Reefer | Temperature-controlled (perishables) |
| 40' Reefer High Cube | Large temperature-controlled shipments |

---

## 7. Commodity Types

Manage the commodity categories customers can select when searching for rates (optional field).

![Commodity Types](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_commodity_types_1773191209855.png)

### Managing Commodity Types

- Click **+ New Type** to add a commodity category
- Each commodity has a **Name** (e.g., "General Cargo", "Garments", "Electronics")
- Use **Edit** / **Del** buttons to manage existing types
- These appear as dropdown options on the public rates search form

---

## 8. Pricing Tiers

Configure the pricing tier system that controls rate visibility per customer.

![Pricing Tiers](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_pricing_tiers_1773191213698.png)

### How Tiers Work

```
Public rates → Visible to everyone (even non-logged-in visitors)
Tier 1 rates → Only visible to customers assigned to Tier 1
Tier 2 rates → Only visible to customers assigned to Tier 2
...and so on
```

### Managing Tiers

- Click **+ New Tier** to create a pricing tier
- Each tier has a **Name** (e.g., "Tier 1", "VIP", "Preferred")
- Assign customers to tiers via [User Management](#4-user-management)
- Create rate entries with specific tier visibility via [Rate Management](#3-rate-management)

> [!TIP]
> Use pricing tiers to offer competitive rates to key accounts while keeping standard public pricing visible to new visitors. A customer on "Tier 1" sees both public rates AND their exclusive Tier 1 rates.

