## 9. Audit Log

A complete, read-only log of every change made in the admin panel. Useful for tracking who changed what and when.

![Audit Log](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_audit_log_1773191254138.png)

### Audit Log Columns

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Timestamp** | Exact date and time of the change |
| **Table** | Which data was changed (Rates, Profiles, etc.) |
| **Action** | Type of change — INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE |
| **Record ID** | Unique identifier of the affected record |
| **Performed By** | Email of the admin who made the change |

### Viewing Details

Click the **View** button on any row to see a detailed, formatted modal showing:

- **What was changed** — field-by-field breakdown
- **Old vs. New values** — for UPDATE actions, changed fields are highlighted in amber
- **Full record data** — for INSERT and DELETE actions

> [!NOTE]
> The audit log is read-only and cannot be modified or deleted. It provides a complete accountability trail for all administrative actions.

---

## 10. Settings

Configure system-wide platform settings.

![Platform Settings](/Users/yujithperera/.gemini/antigravity/brain/86bfbafd-d417-468b-ba06-160d77b000d7/screenshot_settings_1773191257949.png)

### Bill of Lading (B/L) Fee

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **Amount (USD)** | The B/L fee added to every booking request's grand total |

- Enter the fee amount in USD
- Click **Save B/L Fee** to update
- This fee is shown on the public rates page as a separate line item

### Booking Contact Emails

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| **Email Addresses** | List of email addresses that receive booking request notifications |

- Enter one email address per line
- Click **Save Emails** to update
- When a customer submits a booking request, all listed email addresses receive the notification
- Employee emails are **never exposed** to customers

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Make sure at least one valid email address is configured here. If no emails are set, booking notifications will fall back to the default address.

---

## 11. Booking Email Notifications

When a customer submits a booking request through the rates page, the system:

1. **Sends a branded HTML email** to all addresses configured in Settings → Booking Contact Emails
2. **Does NOT expose** any employee email addresses to the customer
3. The email includes:
   - Route details (origin → destination)
   - Shipment details (container type, quantity, rates)
   - Customer contact information
   - A **"Reply to Customer"** button for easy response
4. Each email has a **unique reference ID** in the subject line (e.g., `[GL-20260311-1430]`) for easy tracking

### What the Customer Sees

When they click "Send Booking Request":
- A loading spinner appears on the button
- On success: a green confirmation message — *"Booking request sent! We'll get back to you within 24 hours."*
- The modal closes automatically after 3 seconds
- On failure: an error message appears with details

---

## Quick Reference

### Workflow: Adding a New Rate

1. **Ports** → Ensure both origin and destination ports exist
2. **Container Types** → Ensure the container type exists
3. **Pricing Tiers** → Ensure the target tier exists
4. **Rates** → Click **+ New Rate**, fill in details, save

### Workflow: Onboarding a New Customer with Preferred Pricing

1. **Pricing Tiers** → Create a tier if needed (e.g., "Preferred")
2. **Users** → Find the customer → **Edit** → Set their tier to "Preferred"
3. **Rates** → Create rates with tier = "Preferred" for their specific routes
4. Customer now sees their exclusive rates when logged in

### Workflow: Investigating a Change

1. **Audit Log** → Filter or scroll to find the timestamp
2. Click **View** to see the full change details
3. Check **Performed By** to identify who made the change
4. Review **Old vs. New values** for UPDATE actions

---

